Database & Logic Rules

Schema Generation

Source of Truth: Refer to the "Database Schema" section in the PRD for all table and column names.

SQL Generation: Always generate valid PostgreSQL/Supabase SQL for any new tables or Row Level Security policies.

Naming: Use snake_case for database columns and PascalCase for TypeScript interfaces.

Server Actions & Mutations

All database writes (POST/PATCH/DELETE) must be handled via Next.js Server Actions ('use server').

Use Zod for server-side validation on every form submission.

Every mutation must be guarded by an identity check using supabase.auth.getUser().

Data Handling

Currency: Store financial values as numeric or integer (representing kobo) to avoid rounding errors. Default currency is NGN (₦).

Enums: Use the exact status strings from the PRD (e.g., pending, active, sold, archived).

Images: Upload images to Supabase Storage buckets. Store only the URL strings in the database tables.